# Prettier ignore — aligns `bun run format` / `bun run format:check` with the
# CI gate-08 scope (src/**/*.ts, schemas/**/*.json, templates/**/*.json).
#
# Rationale for each exclusion category:
#
# Markdown (*.md): Prettier reformats prose, rewraps tables, and alters
# heading/list structure in ways that are lossy for curated authoring content
# (ADRs, docs, CLAUDE.md authority files, skills, agents). Markdown formatting
# is enforced by markdownlint (gate-10) which checks structure without mangling
# prose. Adding prettier on top creates two competing formatters for .md.
#
# Dev-apparatus JSON (.claude/): Lives in .claude/ and never ships
# (TEAM-BRIEF §5 "Do not pollute the shipped tree with dev apparatus").
# Formatting run-artifacts (audit-findings, oop-glossary, eval/runs) can alter
# the byte-exact fixtures that tests compare against.
#
# Vault and raw data (docs/vault-example/, docs/claude-wiki-pages-plugin-vault/,
# tests/eval/runs/): These are data files — LLM outputs, vault content, eval
# artifacts. Reformatting them would corrupt or alter factual meaning.
#
# The CI gate (gate-08-prettier.sh) enforces:
#   src/**/*.ts, schemas/**/*.json, templates/**/*.json
# This file makes `bun run format:check` agree with that scope.

# Markdown — linted by markdownlint (gate-10), not prettier
**/*.md

# Dev-apparatus and plugin configuration (never shipped)
.claude/
.claude-plugin/

# Vault data, raw content, and eval artifacts (data, not code)
docs/vault-example/
docs/claude-wiki-pages-plugin-vault/
skills/init/template/
tests/eval/
tests/fixtures/
